AskBrien was formed as a business resource by Lindsay Mann and Peter Bronstein in California. At AskBrien, we realized early on that businesses have limited options to get answers to their business questions. While outside consultants and coaches are available the costs of such services can range from a few hundred dollars to thousands of dollars per hour! With millions of business owners unable to obtain free advice there was a huge need. People also like the idea of a community of businesses which is why the AskBrien.com community was created. The Company will first and always provide answers to business questions and allow users to answer questions. By being a business owners past, present or future, many of the same business issues will arise. When you can go to someone who has previously experienced the same or similar issue, then you can learn the pros and cons of the circumstances and can often avoid pitfalls. AskBrien.com is based in Los Angeles, California and has a technology team of seven, with over 30 years of experience.

Description: Biozek Medical is a leading biotechnology company based in the Netherlands.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Biozek Medical is a Netherlands-based biotechnology company that specializes in the research and development of medical diagnostic and immunodiagnostic tools and point of care test kits. It provides innovative solutions for medical communities worldwide through the combination of Biozek rapid tests and the latest electronic tools. Biozek manufactures a wide range of in vitro diagnostic (IVD) products, working with recognized suppliers of medical equipment to provide its clients with cost effective and accurate testing products. Biozek is well known in the medical community as a solution provider company. Seeking to assist medical institutions in more effectively handling the current pandemic, Biozek has created several rapid tests that offer fast and accurate results: the COVID-19 Antibody Rapid Test, using serum or plasma samples, and two COVID-19 Antigen Rapid Tests that use nasal swabs, throat swabs, or saliva samples.  Through its creation of new technological platforms and business processes, Biozek has tapped into new techno-commercial areas of the point of care testing market. It teams with well-recognized suppliers of medical equipment to provide its customers with highly accurate and cost effective testing products. Biozek Medical has evolved into a global leader in the manufacture of in vitro diagnostic products. The Biozek rapid test for COVID-19 and its tests for other infectious diseases are regarded as world class products.    Biozek has leveraged the increased interest in point of care testing solutions, due to an increased specialization in medical facilities and the further decentralization of hospitals. Its commitment to manufacturing the highest quality products and pursuing effective and innovative solutions has helped Biozek to build strong partnerships and to grow a loyal customer base. It continues to improve the availability of high quality medical equipment and diagnostic tools with developing countries and to create a better workflow for point of care institutions.

Full Description: MNSureThing is both an informational resource and a place where Minnesotans can receive individualized help related to MNsure.org (the Minnesota health insurance exchange marketplace) and the implementation of the Affordable Care Act in Minnesota.   MNSureThing covers how the Affordable Care Act (ACA) will affect folks in Minnesota while offering individualized help when needed. On January 1st, 2014, major changes will be implemented due to the healthcare law; none more important to the potential success of the ACA and the healthcare reform goals than the creation of state health insurance exchanges.  The Minnesota exchange at MNsure.org, and all other state exchanges, will be an online marketplace that will allow individuals, families and small business owners the opportunity to comparison shop and purchase health insurance.  The application process for Medicaid and MinnesotaCare will also take place at MNsure starting this year.  One of the goals of the state exchanges is to become a "one-stop-shop" for every possible health insurance option except for Medicare. MNSureThing will provide extensive information on the Minnesota health insurance marketplace at MNsure; the information focused entirely on the health insurance plans available won't be "completed" until after October 1st, 2013, when MNsure officially opens for business.  All of the specific health insurance plan information won't be made public until that date.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: OSSPolice provides a suite of web services intended to automate open-source software risk management. Open-Source Software (OSS), offering substantially reduced costs and times to develop, has become increasingly popular for companies in recent years. However, bugs and vulnerabilities can jeopardize not only the effectiveness of the software but also endanger sensitive data and provide an opening for hackers to propagate malware. Businesses today are forced to spend resources thoroughly analyzing OSS packages for code quality and security risks before importing them. OSSPolice, built over the years as part of two doctoral dissertations, can swiftly vet OSS packages for both known security risks and underlying code weaknesses. This comprehensive risk-assessment package is far superior to existing services, shortening analysis from days to minutes, and giving 10x higher selection confidence. The customer for OSSPolice is hypothesized to be medium-sized firms in highly regulated industries (finance, healthcare, etc.). OSSPolice has demonstrated its superiority by collecting 135,000 OSS packages and analyzing 1.6 million Android apps to flag over 100,000 apps with severe vulnerabilities.

Full Description: Lawditor was formed by a group of attorneys and tech geeks who realized the availability of quality legal information is most limited by one thing: cost. When a client comes to a lawyer with a legal problem, the lawyer knows the right questions to ask (or can find them) in order to help the client. But what happens when the client doesn’t yet know he or she has a problem? That’s why legal audits were created in the first place: to ask questions targeting common legal problems to inform clients of problems that haven’t yet reached the lawsuit stage. Lawditor maintains a knowledge base of quality legal research, utilizes software with conditional branching logic (later questions are different based on earlier answers), and makes legal compliance audits affordable for every business.
